    • CNFABW2NBWConverter

      public CNFABW2NBWConverter​(java.util.Hashtable<State,​Pair<State,​java.lang.Integer>> table)
      The argument table is a mapping from a state in WAA to a pair of a state in UCB and the rank. This table can be utilized to perform some simplification in complementation via weak alternating automata.
      Parameters:
      table - a mapping from a state in WAA to a pair of a state in UCB and the rank

  • Method Details

    • cnfABW2NBW

      public FSA cnfABW2NBW​(AltAutomaton aa) throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
      Convert an alternating Büchi automaton to a nondeterministic Büchi automaton. This algorithm is from [Miyano and Hayashi 1984].
      Parameters:
      aa - a CNF style alternating Büchi automaton
      Returns:
      an equivalent nondeterministic Büchi automaton
      Throws:
      java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the automaton aa is not a CNF style alternating Büchi automaton
